#: ../../language/error_codes/E0006.md:1
msgid "E0006"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0006.md:3
msgid "Warning name: `unused_constructor`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0006.md:5
msgid "Variant is never read, never constructed, or both."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0006.md:7
msgid ""
"If a variant is never read, it means it is defined but never destructed "
"in a pattern matching expression (`match`, `let`, `guard let`, loop "
"function, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0006.md:10
msgid "If a variant `A` is never constructed, it means there is no `A(...)`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0006.md:11
msgid "If a variant is unused, it means it is never constructed and never read."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0006.md:13
msgid "Erroneous example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0006.md:15
msgid ""
"///|\n"
"priv enum T {\n"
"  A\n"
"  B\n"
"  C\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"///|\n"
"pub fn f() -> Unit {\n"
"  match T::A {\n"
"    B => ()\n"
"    _ => ()\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0006.md:19
msgid "Suggestion"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0006.md:21
msgid ""
"If some variants are never read, while others are read, this means that "
"you have use wildcard pattern (`_`) in your code. You can expand the "
"wildcard pattern to include the unused variants."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0006.md:25
msgid ""
"\n"
"///|\n"
"priv enum T {\n"
"  A\n"
"  B\n"
"  C\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"///|\n"
"pub fn f() -> Unit {\n"
"  match T::A {\n"
"    B => ()\n"
"    C => ()\n"
"    A => ()\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0006.md:31
msgid ""
"If all variants are never read, and you need to read these variants "
"outside of current package, you can add `pub` keyword to the enum "
"definition. Notice this will make the implementation of the variant "
"visible to the users of the package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0006.md:36
msgid ""
"\n"
"///|\n"
"pub enum T2 {\n"
"  A\n"
"  B\n"
"  C\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"///|\n"
"pub fn T2::new(value : Int) -> T2 {\n"
"  match value {\n"
"    0 => T2::A\n"
"    1 => T2::B\n"
"    _ => T2::C\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0006.md:42
msgid ""
"If you need to construct the \"never constructed\" variant outside of the"
" current package, you can add `pub(all)` keyword to the variant."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0006.md:45
msgid ""
"\n"
"///|\n"
"pub(all) enum T3 {\n"
"  A\n"
"  B\n"
"  C\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0006.md:51
msgid "If some variants are indeed useless, you can remove the unused variants."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0006.md:53
msgid ""
"\n"
"///|\n"
"priv enum T4 {\n"
"  A\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"///|\n"
"pub fn g() -> Unit {\n"
"  match T4::A {\n"
"    A => ()\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

